Let $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -5 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\mathbf{w} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -7 \end{pmatrix}.$  Then the projection of $\mathbf{v}$ onto $\mathbf{w}$ is
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v} = \frac{\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{w}}{\|\mathbf{w}\|^2} \mathbf{w} = \frac{-11}{50} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -7 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} -\frac{11}{50} \\ \frac{77}{50} \end{pmatrix}.\]Therefore, the distance between the two lines is $\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} -\frac{11}{50} \\ \frac{77}{50} \end{pmatrix} \right\| = \boxed{\frac{6 \sqrt{10}}{5}}.$

